  "texts": [
    "As a refinement, we train a sentence classifier (as in Section 7.2) on the training set, using the labels obtained by the sentence similarity approach.",
    "Although this is a supervised learning step, we are not using the original labels, therefore the overall approach is still unsupervised.",
    "The resulting confusion matrix, evaluated on the test set, is shown in the right part of Figure 20.",
    "Compared to the zero-shot classifier, the confusion between \"Vandalism\" and \"Vehicle\" has significantly reduced, and the scores have improved.",
    "This comparison is not entirely fair, because we have not used the same candidate expressions in both cases."
  ],
